QUALIFICATION: Garthopilumnus ?tev?i?, 2005, is an invalid nomen nudum as it was erected without diagnostic characters. ?tev?i? (2005: 133) designated Pilumnus palmeri Garth, 1986, as the type species of Garthopilumnus ?tev?i?, 2005, and commented that it may need to be assigned to its own family ?Garthopilumnidae? - the family name also being unavailable. The genus should be re-evaluated and described only when specimens can be examined.
